 when they don't Nuke 101</span><hr size=1> OK there's a thread about Wizards and grouping, and I thought it would be constructive and helpful for everyone to give their ideas, tactics, concepts, and tricks of what to do when your nukes aren't needed, aren't enough, or just when you want to show off your skills in addition to blowing things up.<br>
<br>
1) Stuns: these are technically damage, but they shouldn't be overlooked.  Until you get Markar's Discord the damage is on the low end, but they are more useful than most give credit.  Stuns make the monsters stop attacking early in the fight (saving damage) make them stop casting any point in the fight, and stop gating at the end of the fight.  They can give people breathing room, such as enchanters and clerics.  They are a good mix to throw in to make sure you are helping your group as much as possible.<br>
<br>
2) Snares: yes, there's 5 other classes with snare (bard, sk, necromancer, ranger, and druid) but they aren't always handy.  Further the AE aspect of your snare actually works out nicely on multiple pulls.  Mezed monsters don't stay that way permanently, and a snared monster stalks the Enchanter slower than a full speed one.  Further, Snares not only stop runners, but they slow aggro from taking effect in a sense: monsters that are snared don't zip around the battlefield at full speed when they get aggro on someone other than the tank, they walk slowly over, giving the tank more time to regain aggro.<br>
<br>
3) Root: again, lots of other classes with root, but yours will tend to be slightly better most levels and further the other classes often have other needs for those 8 spell slots where its not as desparate a situation for you.  Root allows you to control aggro and movement on the battlefield, because rooted monsters will attack whoever is closest to them no matter WHO they hate.  Stopping a monster that the enchanter is being pasted by will allow them to back off and control it better.  Rooting that monster that's runnin amok hitting all the medding people is always appreciated.<br>
<br>
4) Ports and Evacs: the only reason you'll get into groups sometimes, and the reason groups will have to break up when you leave at times.  When you are the only porter deep inside Hate's Fury or Hate, people tend to see you in a better light.  This won't come up much until you are rather high level although the next expansion might make it more useful.  Evacuates have been more or less made useless because of lesser evac (there was never any need for more than one in any case).  Ports will let you get people out of the group or the entire group to safety or a hunting spot better than anyone else in the game when you get high enough level.  When you get Decession you can even fire sleeping group members to the zone.<br>
<br>
5) Skins: these get spendy, but when you are high enough level they'll let you get away with things normally you'd avoid.  The high level skins or epic skin let you take a pretty good hammering and keep going, where many casters would have folded up a while ago.  This means you can walk the aggro line closer (combined with concussion) to keep your damage up in an emergency, as well as take a few hits for the team until they can get things under control.  By the way does it annoy anyone else that they call our skin line &quot;RUNES&quot; in the spell picker?  Jerks.<br>
<br>
6) Stacking: Wizards, along with a handful of other classes in the game, stack more or less infinitely.  You can have 16 Wizards in a raid and none will be sitting around wondering why the hell they even are there (well unless too low level to hurt anything).  16 enchanters is just silly, for example.  <br>
<br>
SO any other thoughts?  Positive ones, that is?<br>
