<br>
1) snare running mobs<br>
2) root park multiple pulls<br>
3) kite the unsnarable adds<br>
4) protect the healer(s) by pulling mobs off<br>
5) protect the MT if you know the ch is late by stunning the mob<br>
<br>
Sure, they are not as elegant as mezz or charm.  But when done properly, they are nevertheless just as effective.  For those that are open and willing, I urge you to learn and perfect these skills.  Once you build a reputation by being versatile and skilled, finding groups and getting help will no longer be a problem. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naeanthesorcerer>NaeanTheSorcerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 5:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards when they don't Nuke 101</span><hr size=1> our snare i think is a waste in an experience group.  because it's AE, it costs a lot of mana, and more often than not, when you're in a group, it's only going to hit one mob.  because of the waste of mana, i don't snare in a group unless i am the only person there that can.  a druid or ranger can snare the mob just as well for 35 mana as i can for 125.<br>
<br>
root i think is a really good spell, except for the people that won't move out of the way when a mob is rooted.  this is especially bad in BoT and other zones where you fight mobs that have really large melee range.  i don't know if they really don't notice two different mobs hitting them or what it is, but a lot of tanks will back a few feet away and act as if the problem is taken care of, meanwhile they're still taking damage from the main mob and the rooted one.<br>
<br>
when your crowd control is just a root (whether done by a wizard or any other root-enabled class) everyone needs to pay attention to where they are standing and where all the mobs are in the camp.  sometimes this requires a little more thought than the ideal situation where a chanter mezzes and the problem is taken care of completely.  all too often, people are not willing (or maybe not able) to expend this little bit of extra effort. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=492380" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/jomarti8/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1964<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 5:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards when they don't Nuke 101</span><hr size=1> the main problem really is, if I have to do support in a group alot instead of just pure DD, the exp in such a group is way slower than in a group were 9 of 10 spells I cast are DD <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
