<br>
Grimmy, you forgot about the PULLING wizard.  The Flux staff is the premier pulling item (low aggro, no damage, always hits, and unlimited clicks) and concussion is the next best thing to FD, especially when combined with a snared MOB who isn't quite at camp yet. <br>
 <br>
Let us not forget about stun pulling as well.  Nothing like a 3 to 8 second head start running back to camp.  I've used this one quite effictively in dungeons (hint: I don't even have run1)<br>
<br>
Then there is my favorite ... ROOT PULLING.  Yes, the perfect way split MOBs.  If your going to have to CC, may as well start by rooting the first and let social aggro pull your first target.  This works REALLY well when you also have an Enc in group who can mem wipe.  <br>
In an 8-person raid on the third floor of Ssra (me being the only INT caster), we used this method when a General had spawned near the entry door rather than having the monk take several minutes splitting them.  <br>
<br>
Outdoor zones are a blast to pull as well.  A good many levels of quadding is some pretty tough places makes you figure out how to get MOBs to avoid getting too close to other pathing things.<br>
<br>
Fredre <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 6:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I really think you covered allmost all the extra stuff a wizard can be doing, Grimstaff.<br>
<br>
My personal favorite is using Stun when I see a CH heall call. 6 extra seconds is alot, and has made a difference between life and death for groups I've been in.<br>
<br>
When we have our enchanter friend with us, he always AE mezzes, then remezzes single targets. I AE snare and then root the mobs he's mezzing. By this time, the tank had aggro nice and good, and I can nuke has much as I want. <br>
<br>
Sometimes we have a second wizard with us. Two wizards in a group completely change everything, let me tell you. Using alternating stuns and DD, the both of you can burn down a mob, and keep it doing very little, while the rest of the group beats the crap out of it. <br>
<br>
But don't expect much credit. People seldom focus on whats going on besides what they are doing. Many won't realize that your stun as the CH was called probably was what allowed it to land on time part of the time. That you stun stopped the mob from Healing it's self or gating. <br>
<br>
Yes, roots are great, and when they don't move away from a rooted mob, it's not effective. First, try and lessen this from happening by telling them what you are planning on doing before fighting. Second, either have it in your hotkey setup, or a social key made to tell them to back up.<br>
<br>
I've used the eye of zomm to see if the way ahead was clear in places I know there are wandering mobs. And your right, in new zones, or revamped zones, they rock. You can also use it to target a mob in an area with multiple mobs and have a cleric pacify one, if you can't get viusally close enough for the cleric to do it. There by making it easy for the puller to do his job. <br>
<br>
But at the same time, don't expect any congratulations from many people for what you do, since they won't see it or what realize at first how helpful you really are.<br>
<br>
I think that is the biggest challenge of playing a wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27059.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27059.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27059.topic&start=61&stop=65>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27059.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27059.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notific